==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[tablette]]'', diminutive of ''[[table#French|table]]'', "table".
===Noun===
'''tablet''' (''plural:'' '''tablets''')
# a small [[portion]] of a [[drug]] or other [[substance]]s to be taken [[oral]]ly, of [[cylindrical]] [[shape]], about three millimeter in height and about one centimeter in diameter
#:''Many people take vitamin '''tablets''' as a food supplement.''
# A [[slab]] of [[rock]] used for [[inscription]].
====Synonyms====
#[[pill]]
